      <main class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds" role="main" id="main">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Connect to GovWifi</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">
          Sign up and you'll be able to connect to the internet automatically in any building that has GovWifi.
        </p>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">1. Create a GovWifi account</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">You need a public sector email address to create a GovWifi account.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">Use your public sector email address to:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>send a blank email to <%= link_to "signup@wifi.service.gov.uk", "mailto:signup@wifi.service.gov.uk", class: "govuk-link" %></li>
          <li>leave the subject line blank</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="govuk-body">We’ll reply with your username and password.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">Check your spam or junk email folder if the email doesn’t come through in a few minutes.</p>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">2. Connect your device</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">By connecting to GovWifi, you accept our <a class="govuk-link" href="/privacy-notice">privacy notice</a> and <a href="/terms-and-conditions" class="govuk-link">terms and conditions</a>.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">To connect your device:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>go to your device wifi settings and select GovWifi</li>
          <li>enter the username and password we sent you</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="govuk-body">You can use the same password to connect all your devices to GovWifi.</p>
        <p class="govuk-body">Do not share your password with anyone else.</p>
      </main>
